criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of COPD based on the GOLD criteria - postbronchodilator forced expiratory
             volume in 1 second (FEV1)/forced vital capacity (FVC) ratio <70%;

          -  Electrocardiogram (ECG) record at rest;

          -  Written informed consent form;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of any clinical condition that does not allow the participants to a
             home-based PR program, such as, significant cardiovascular (e.g. symptomatic ischaemic
             cardiac disease), neurological (e.g. neuromuscular dystrophy disease), or presence of
             musculoskeletal disease;

          -  Signs of cognitive impairment (e.g. dementia).
